metadata.name: Obscured by Clouds #82
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to create a painterly texture and to keep the focus on just the paint rather than any object it fills. It's coded in p5.js and uses overlapping translucent shapes to create the texture.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called 'Obscured by Clouds' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/track/3c8LKbUsjW9lMYQzVScXQT
Press 's' to save the image

Credits:
 - Technique is inspired by this essay by Tyler Hobbs: https://tylerxhobbs.com/essays/2020/how-to-hack-a-painting
 - The name of the artwork is a tribute to my favourite band

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #2394
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.

metadata.name: (kinder)Garden, Monuments #232
metadata.description:
When Yazid and Zancan started their fxcollab journey, they knew very little about each other. They learnt about their rich cultural differences, their complementary graphic styles, and a 7-hour timezone difference. What they did have in common was each had two kids about the same age (one a pair of girls, the other boys).

Every kid was born a builder; every kid likes to sit in nature. It’s their way of discovering the world and dreaming of their future accomplishments. While they marvel at the heights of the cities and monuments they construct out of stacks of cubes, parents marvel at their ability to elaborate an unlimited range of worlds out of a limited range of materials. 

This project celebrates the humble and versatile cube. A deceptively simple yet powerful object of play and learning, regardless of age, whether you’re stacking them up in a sandbox, or learning 3D graphics for the first time. 

This project is dedicated to kids, those who were once children, to the dreamers and builders who still enjoy playing with cubes.

Coded in Vanilla JS, the project combines Yazid's iconic “Hashed/Hatched” aesthetic incorporated into childhood wooden toy block structures, and Zancan's signature lush foliage and framework, which enables all iterations to be plottable.
 
Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to get a SVG file suited for plotters
- Click on the image to download a 4K resolution PNG

metadata.name: Lineas #157
metadata.description:
Búscame entre mis letras por que en ellas siempre voy a estar
y en los versos de mis poemas mi corazón escucharás...

Lee cada palabra que encuentres donde quieres buscar
esas que ya conoces y que además te hacen extrañar.
Si te emocionan sueña siempre con algo más, no llores
por que existe un camino donde las letras tienen su punto y final.

El amor es un poema o un milagro terrenal, es la magia
que nos envuelve a los que nos podemos enamorar.
Amar cuesta y cuando se ama duele, se sufre, se llora
por el ser amado, eso es lo que tu alma atesora.

Cada verso que escribo lleva en su contenido un significado,
una promesa, un abrazo entre líneas y un beso de enamorado...

AMOR ENTRE LÍNEAS.
poema de De Lorenzo Román.

-----

Press 'e' to export a 1640 x 2000 pixels PNG

Press 'h' to export a 3280 x 4000 pixels PNG

-----



Artwork by @cristianrohr 2022.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Minimal #7
metadata.description:
Created to a prompt of "minimal," this piece features a variable number of overlayed rectangles, some with stripes, slowly rotating as their colors gradually shift. The result is a relaxing dynamic piece that is constantly changing.

Press the space bar to export a 4000x4000 png still image.

metadata.name: Dump of links #52
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork.
A blind spot in the metaverse full of junk broken links. Like dead neurons, they were left out of the system. Now they look for the closest thing to oxygen, and in a sonorous broken prelude, achieve synchro, so that one or at least two escape.

The work has 3 moments:
I. "Preludio en el fondo"
II. "Respiración de rotos"
III. "Grita y quema"

Original processed piano, flute and electronic samplers.
((click to start sound))

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)

metadata.name: Stack of Shapes #52
metadata.description:
Inspired by sketches I'd draw in my college notebook during class. This piece uses a hand-drawn stroke style to draw a stack of overlapping shapes. Look closely and see that the lines are made of thousands of tiny dots. Iterations vary by color scheme, background color, line thickness, density, and more, with a small chance of using a rainbow color palette.  
  
Press R to re-run the drawing animation; enter to save the image in high quality. Enjoy!

metadata.name: Shine On You Crazy Diamond #8
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to depict lights seen through textured and coloured glass windows. It's coded entirely in p5.js and is made of only rectangles, thousands of them.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called ‘Shine On You Crazy Diamond Parts I-V' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/track/6pnwfWyaWjQiHCKTiZLItr

Artwork loads at 1000px by 1000px resolution by default. Press ‘2’,’4’ or ‘8’ to load as 2000px by 2000px, 4000px by 4000px or 8000px by 8000px respectively.
Press 's' at any time to download the rendered resolution.

Credits:
- Landed on this technique when experimenting with ideas in this essay by Tyler Hobbs: https://tylerxhobbs.com/essays/2015/creating-soft-textures-generatively
- Although my logic to create grids is slightly different, this blog by Gorilla Sun was a good starting point & guide: https://gorillasun.de/blog/an-algorithm-for-irregular-grids
- The name of the artwork is a tribute to my favourite band

metadata.name: StairWaves #137
metadata.description:
StairWaves is a generative collection imagining abstract stairs built in a wavy nature, with shadows being a key theme. While some waves are quite turbulent, others are just flat.

All shapes in the artwork are built using the same core logic applied in different ways. The method used to draw the waves is also used to draw the shadows, as well as the subtle textures on the surface of the waves. This homogeneous approach ensures a consistent and flowy feel to the final output.

StairWaves is coded entirely in p5.js. 

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)

metadata.name: La Pedrera Serie 1 #252
metadata.description:
This project is inspired from Gaudí's Casa Milà in Barcelona, also known as La Pedrera. 

This is the first part of a 2-part-serie based on La Pedrera.

In this project, which is intentionaly saturated in color, you will recognize an abstract reproduction of the curved floors and windows of La Casa Milà.

The colors are accentued by the flowers disseminated on each floor. 

Main features of this project include:
- Palette: 10 colors,
- Texture: Strong or Soft,
- Noise: True or False,
- Strong Lines: True or False,
- Flower Packing: Mini or Maxi.

In live mode, press [s] to save a 1200 x 1500 (4 DPI) version of the mint.

Thanks a lot to everyone who will mint a token! :)

metadata.name: Women in art #25
metadata.description:
According to Women Can't Paint, a book by Helen Gorrill, paintings made by men sell for 10x as much as women's paintings.

This piece is one of two conceptual generative artworks. One is called "Men in art", the other "Women in art". They are identical except for two differences:
1. The dithering filter in "Men in art" favors blue colors over red ones, while "Women in art" do the opposite.
2. The price of "Men in art" is 10 tez, while "Women in art" is priced at 1 tez.

Made with p5.js, Typescript and Fettepalette.

There is a secret key, which removes the dithering filter.
